http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Campaign-for-orphans/article13975841.ece

Minister for Social Welfare M. K. Muneer inaugurated the ‘Snehapoorvam Sahapadiku’ campaign of the Kerala Social Security Mission here on Friday.The aim of the initiative is to support the educational needs of orphaned children and provide social protection to them. People who participated in the programme took a pledge to extend a helping hand to the children through various social security projects.A campaign will be on till January 26 to collect funds for the implementation of the project. More details about the welfare programme could be had fromwww.socialsecuritymission.gov.in